{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Filo stacks","content":["Place Brazil nuts into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 6<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place butter into mixing bowl and melt <b>2 min\/90°C\/speed 2<b>. Transfer into a separate bowl and set aside.","Preheat oven to 190°C. Line a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Place 1 sheet of the filo pastry onto a silicone bread mat or clean work surface and brush with reserved melted butter. Scatter with one-quarter of the reserved Brazil nuts and, using a fine-mesh sieve, dust with 1 tablespoon of the icing sugar. Place a second sheet of the filo pastry on top and brush with butter, scatter with another one-quarter of the Brazil nuts and dust with another 1 tablespoon of the icing sugar. Repeat the process twice more until you have 4 stacked sheets, finishing in a sprinkling of nuts and icing sugar. Cut into 16 squares (approx. 8 x 7 cm) and place onto prepared baking tray. Bake for 8-10 minutes (190°C) or until golden brown. Remove filo stacks from oven and dust immediately with remaining 1 tablespoon icing sugar. Set aside to cool. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Berry and cream filling","content":[" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream, mascarpone, vanilla and icing sugar into mixing bowl and whip <b>30 sec\/speed 3<b> until firm, watching carefully through hole in mixing bowl lid to avoid over whipping. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>.","To assemble, place 8 of the filo squares onto a serving platter or individual serving plates. Top each square with 2 tablespoons of the cream mixture and half of the sliced strawberries. Place remaining 8 filo squares on top of strawberries and cream, pushing down gently. Top filo stacks with remaining cream and strawberries, then garnish with mint leaves (optional) to serve (see Tips)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Filo stacks","content":["80 g shelled Brazil nuts (see Tips)","60 g unsalted butter, cut into pieces","4 sheets filo pastry","5 tbsp icing sugar"]},{"title":"Berry and cream filling","content":["200 g thickened cream","100 g mascarpone cheese","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","2 tbsp icing sugar","120 g strawberries, trimmed and cut into thin slices (see Tips)","fresh mint leaves only, for garnishing (optional)"]}],"id":"r250032","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-KfDrjTT0d0s\/XZWeQ-4PESI\/AAAAAAAAexk\/UOGSRqLyNxY56WHnYp-zg1ellz9nOMxrACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_WiccQlEyN9aUS7M6.png","title":"Berry and cream filo stacks","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.5 g","fat":"27.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"19.9 g","calories":"1413.6 kJ \/ 336.6 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, silicone bread mat, pastry brush, fine-mesh sieve, serving platter, oven","hintsAndTricks":["You can use nuts and fresh fruit of choice in this recipe. We used Brazil nuts for the unique flavour and texture.","You can assemble this dish up to 1 hour before serving."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","30m","8 portions"]}